    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "In trying to force others to carry out your ideas in every particular, you often do greater harm than if you were to yield these points. This is true even when your ideas are right in themselves, but in many things they are not correct; they are overstrained as the result of the <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"226\"></span> peculiarities of your organization; therefore you drive the wrong thing in a strong, unreasonable manner.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">3<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Lt 19a, 1891\" data-link=\"14057.5977001\">Letter 19a, 1891</span>.</span></a></sup>",
